            <div class="margin-top-24">
                <h3>Bad to the Bone: Medications Associated with Increased Fracture Risk </h3>
                <p></p><h3>
                    ABOUT:
                </h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>This clinically relevant and interactive (case-based) program was developed by leading Canadian experts to address the importance of risk assessment, screening and management for all patients at high-risk for fracture with the particular focus on the use of medications that are associated with bone loss, osteoporosis, and fragility fractures. This program aims to translate scientific and clinical evidence into practical steps and incorporates expert recommendations into practical strategies applicable to primary care practice.</li>
                </ul>
                <p></p><h3>
                    FORMAT:
                </h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            This program consists of introductory slides and 5 case vignettes specific to medications associated with bone loss and increased fracture risk. <br>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            The presenter can present all or some of the vignettes and additionally may utilize the back-up slides for program certified for 1.5 Mainpro+ credits. <br>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>Please decide whether the condensed or extended version of the program will be presented prior to submitting the New Event Request Form.</p>
                    </li>
                </ul>
                <p></p><h3>CERTIFICATION:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>This Group Learning activity      has been certified for up to 1.5 MAINPRO+ one-credit-per-hour credits by      the CFPC.</li>
                </ul>
                <p></p><h3>
                    SPEAKERS:
                </h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Program speakers will have      access to the program materials once they confirm availability for at      least one of regional event dates</li>
                    <li>A copy of their COI slides is      available in their resource centre for download</li>
                    <li>Please reference the Process      Manual for important information and requirements</li>
                    <li><strong>As per the CFPC guidelines for      certified programs, speakers are required to use the presentation slides      provided by the physician organization and are not permitted to make any      changes to the program materials/slides.</strong></li>
                </ul>
